    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-20T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/10–2048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-20T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 20, 1948—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>935. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 416. Have consulted Critchley and
                        <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> chairman Herremans again regarding
                    question <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> telegram dated October 12 to <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> President<note n="1" xml:id="d335fn1">See
                        telegram 906, October 12, <ref target="#pg_411">p. 411</ref>.</note> (<gloss
                        target="#t_Usgoc1">Usgoc</gloss> 175<note n="2" xml:id="d335fn2">Telegram
                        518, October 19, 4 p. m., not printed.</note>). They expressed view that
                    upon receipt telegram from chairman Repub delegate (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1"
                        >Gocus</gloss> 407<note n="3" xml:id="d335fn3">Telegram 905, October 12,
                            <ref target="#pg_408">p. 408</ref>.</note>) <gloss target="#t_GOC1"
                        >GOC</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0440" n="426" xml:id="pg_426"/> was obliged under its own procedure
                        (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 203 March 25) inform <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> its comments Repub special report would be
                    forthcoming.</p>
                <p>I argued that possibility existed Repub might not present special report and that
                    if special report were not presented, reference to it in <gloss target="#t_GOC1"
                        >GOC</gloss> telegram October 12 to President <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> would only confuse matters. They have agreed that following
                    telegram be sent Protitch.<note n="4" xml:id="d335fn4">D. Protitch, Principal
                        Director of the Department of Security Council Affairs, <gloss
                            target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Secretariat.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Please cancel telegram sent President dated 12 October which is superseded
                        by following telegram dated October 20.</p>
                    <p>“President <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. The <gloss target="#t_GOC1"
                            >GOC</gloss> has honor state it is proceeding with drafting of its
                        fourth interim report. <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> is of opinion
                        that it will be able to report results of Corn’s present endeavors in
                        connection with resumption of full scale negotiations in very near future.
                        For this reason Com will delay submission of its fourth interim report so
                        that the report will present a balanced and comprehensive account of recent
                        developments. Signed Herremans.” Signed Scott.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Department pass Hague and <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">GADel</gloss> Paris.<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d335fn5">Repeated to The Hague and Paris on October 30.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
